Interface CloseableIterator<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - A generic for the type of data for iteration
    All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Closeable, Iterator<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AccumuloSecondaryIndexEntryIteratorWrapper, AccumuloSecondaryIndexJoinEntryIteratorWrapper, CassandraStatisticsIterator, CloseableIterator.Empty, CloseableIterator.Wrapper, CloseableIteratorWrapper, DynamoDBStatisticsIterator, FeatureTranslatingIterator, GPXConsumer, SecondaryIndexEntryIteratorWrapper, SimpleFeatureGeoWaveWrapper

    public interface CloseableIterator<E>
extends Iterator<E>, Closeable
    This interface wraps both the Iterator interface and the Closeable interface. It is best to close an iterator of this interface when it is no longer needed.
